item.title: General HR Analytics and Project Execution Practitioner - Upwork
item.description:
Problem Statement:
Our organization is managing 8-10 key HR initiatives concurrently and requires a highly skilled consultant to provide support in analytics, data visualization, communication development, and PowerPoint presentation creation. The initiatives cover a broad spectrum of HR activities, including enterprise budget processes, utilization targets, skills and resource capacity, organizational structure, compensation, HR operations data architecture, culture and equity plan development, and HR people analytics.
Desired Outcome:
The desired outcome for this role is the seamless execution and support of all HR initiatives, ensuring each project meets its objectives and deadlines. The consultant will deliver comprehensive analytical insights, create effective data visualizations, develop clear communication materials, and support the development of high-quality PowerPoint presentations.

Scope and Deliverables:

Providing analytical support and data visualization for key HR initiatives, including:
Enterprise Budget Process
Utilization Targets Setting
Skills & Resource Capacity
Organizational Structure
Compensation
HR Operations Data Architecture
Culture and Equity Plan Development
HR People Analytics
HR Project Management
End-of-Year Performance Reviews
End-of-Year Open Enrollment
Developing clear and effective communication materials
Creating high-quality PowerPoint presentations for various HR initiatives
Collaborating with HR teams to ensure alignment and integration of initiatives
Monitoring project progress and addressing any issues promptly

Tangible Deliverables:
Detailed project plans and timelines
Comprehensive data analysis, reporting and strategic recommendations
Effective data visualizations and dashboards
Developed communication materials (emails, memos, reports)
High-quality PowerPoint presentations for internal and external stakeholders
Successfully managed end-of-year performance reviews and open enrollment processes
Expert Qualifications:
The ideal expert for this role should possess the following qualifications:
Extensive experience in HR project management and execution
Strong analytical skills and proficiency in HR people analytics
Expertise in data visualization tools (e.g., Tableau, Power BI)
Super proficiency in Excel, including advanced functions, data analysis, and visualization
Proven track record in developing clear and effective communication materials
Advanced skills in PowerPoint presentation development
Experience working with disparate systems and integrating data from various sources
Excellent communication and collaboration skills
Strong project management skills, with the ability to deliver results under tight deadlines



Posted On: July 13, 2024 07:24 UTC
Category: Management Consulting
Skills:Organizational Design & Effectiveness, Microsoft Excel, Project Management, Communications, Presentation Design, Total Compensation Structuring
Skills: Organizational Design & Effectiveness, Microsoft Excel, Project Management, Communications, Presentation Design, Total Compensation Structuring

item.title: Data Integration Specialist - Upwork
item.description:
Our dental practice is seeking a highly skilled Data Integration Specialist to gather, compile, and analyze data from various sources. The ideal candidate will have experience working with diverse data systems such as our dental practice management software (EagleSoft), call center software (CallRail), Google Ads, Google Analytics, social media platforms, internal Excel sheets, HR software, inventory software, and more. The goal is to integrate all these data sources into a unified system like Power BI to generate detailed reports and insights that will enhance overall practice performance through effective use of business intelligence.

Key Responsibilities:
- Data Gathering: Collect data from a variety of sources including EagleSoft, CallRail, Google Ads, Google Analytics, social media platforms, Excel spreadsheets, HR software, and inventory software. Additionally, suggest other data sources we can include that could benefit our practice.

- Data Integration: Import and integrate data into a centralized data software platform such as Power BI.

- Data Organization: Organize and structure the data to ensure it is accurate, consistent, and ready for analysis.

- Analysis & Reporting: Generate detailed reports, identify trends, and provide actionable insights to support strategic decision-making.

- Data Cleaning: Ensure data quality by identifying and rectifying errors, inconsistencies, and missing values.

- Collaboration: Work closely with the dental practice’s management team to understand data needs and deliver insights accordingly.

- Compliance: Ensure all data handling practices comply with relevant privacy and security regulations, particularly those related to patient information.

Qualifications:
Education: Bachelor's degree in Data Science, Computer Science, Information Systems, or a related field.

Experience: Proven experience in data integration, analysis, and reporting. Experience with healthcare or dental practice data is a plus.

Technical Skills: Proficiency in data integration tools (e.g., Power BI), SQL, Excel, and familiarity with management softwares and other relevant platforms.

Analytical Skills: Strong analytical skills with the ability to interpret complex data sets and generate actionable insights.

Communication: Excellent communication skills to effectively convey data findings to non-technical stakeholders.

Attention to Detail: High level of accuracy and attention to detail in data handling and reporting.

item.title: Data Factory/Azure Data Engineering - Upwork
item.description:
Key Responsibilities
• Assist in creating Technical Document as set out in the Solution Design Document
• Deploy and administer Azure Data Lake Storage, Azure SQL Server, Azure Data Factory, Logic Apps, Azure Functions, Virtual Machines
• Set up Linked Services and Integration Runtimes in Azure Data Factory
• Create ETL solutions using Data Flows in Azure Data Factory
• Responsible for Azure data processing including Logic Apps and Azure Data Factory  
• Develop, maintain, monitor and optimize pipelines and workflows in Azure Data Factory
• Help design Data Lake and Data Warehousing solution on Azure infrastructure
• Responsible for developing Power BI solutions as set out in the Solution Design Document
• Create SQL tables, views and stored procedures to meet project requirements
• Create and design SQL tables following star schema/snowflake data model
• Create and optimize existing queries, table indexes, partitions
• Management of SSIS
• Follow sprints/tasks as directed by the Solutions Architect, providing estimates as needed and communicating technical risks to the project manager.   
• Able to troubleshoot quickly and identify solutions effectively  
• To work closely with our development team, Solutions Architect and Project Managers   

Desired Skills and Experience:
• Intermediate level understanding of cloud concepts and tools
• Demonstratable experience in creating ETL solutions using Azure Data Factory or other cloud-based ETL tool
• Experience/Participated in Technical Document creation
• Understanding of Microsoft Cloud solutions and other 3rd party integrations APIs
• Experience in creating a Data Warehouse/Business Intelligence solution
• Demonstratable experience in designing and using star schema and/or snowflake data model
• Understanding of Dimension and Fact tables
• Demonstratable experience in using and creating T-SQL scripts, views, stored procedures and triggers
• Demonstratable experience of SQL Server Deployment
• Demonstratable experience in using Logic Apps  
• Basic knowledge in using Git and/or other version control systems  
• Development experience that includes some or all of Power Platform services, JavaScript, JSON, TypeScript, C# .NET, Microsoft Azure, Microsoft 365, RESTful Web Services, Power BI, SQL Server, Python  
• Microsoft Certified: Azure Data Engineer Associate, Azure Data Fundamentals, Azure Fundamentals and Analyzing Data with Microsoft Power BI.   
• Self-motivated and able to work independently and in a team environment remotely   
• Excellent communication both written and verbal
